olive oil
1 tin sweetcorn
1 Carrot
1 packet Pork Loin Steaks
1 packet Ginger Paste
1 sachet Sweet Soy Seasoning
1 tsp honey
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet mayonnaise
drizzle vinegar (white  wine or rice wine)
1 packet Crispy Shallots
1 packet coriander

• Drain sweetcorn.
• Grate carrot.
• Slice pork loin steaks into 1cm-thick strips.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat. When oil is hot, cook ginger paste, sweet soy seasoning and pork strips, in batches, until golden, 2-3 minutes.
• Remove the pan off the heat, return all pork to the pan, then add the honey. Toss to coat.

TIP: Cooking the pork in batches over a high heat helps it stay tender

• Meanwhile, combine shredded cabbage mix, carrot, sweetcorn,
mayonnaise and a drizzle of vinegar and olive oil in a large bowl. Season to taste.

• Divide slaw between bowls.
• Top with soy-ginger pork, spooning over any remaining sauce from the pan.
• Sprinkle with crispy shallots and tear over coriander to serve. Enjoy!